-- Zamin, Brazilian Iron Ore Miner, May Have $2.5 Billion London IPO, FT Says
-- Rachel Graham
-- 2010-07-24T09:04:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-24/zamin-brazilian-iron-ore-miner-may-have-2-5-billion-london-ipo-ft-says.html

          
          
             Zamin Ferrous , a miner of  iron ore 
in Brazil, is considering selling shares in London, the
 Financial Times  reported.  
 Zamin may be valued at $2 billion to $2.5 billion, the FT
said, citing an unidentified banker familiar with the company.  
